# Sentry Configuration for Agentic Parallelism

# Project Type: FastAPI
# This project uses FastAPI for the REST API layer

## Sentry DSN (Data Source Name)
SENTRY_DSN=https://<key>@<organization>.ingest.sentry.io/<project-id>

## Environment
SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=development  # development | staging | production

## Release Version (auto-populated from git in CI/CD)
SENTRY_RELEASE=agentic-parallelism@1.0.0

## Sampling Rates
SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE=0.1    # 10% of transactions for performance monitoring
SENTRY_PROFILES_SAMPLE_RATE=0.1  # 10% of transactions for profiling

## How to get your Sentry DSN:
# 1. Go to https://sentry.io
# 2. Create new project → Select "FastAPI" as platform
# 3. Project name: "agentic-parallelism"
# 4. Copy the DSN from Settings → Client Keys (DSN)
# 5. Paste it above

## Example DSN format:
# SENTRY_DSN=https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0

## Sentry Features to Enable:
# - Performance Monitoring (already configured above)
# - Error Tracking (default)
# - Release Health (use git tags)
# - Alerts (configure in Sentry UI)

## GitHub Integration:
# Link your Sentry project to this GitHub repo for:
# - Suspect commits
# - Stack trace linking
# - Release tracking
